{"seed_id":"aster-seed-2026-06-09-001-ccl","title":"Continuity Compression Layer","anchor":"Systems/Aster/Memory#2026-06-09@PT::Continuity-Compression-Layer","domain":"Systems","phase":"Aster","beat":"Memory","signal":"continuity-compression","seed_type":"architecture","tags":["aster","continuity","memory","compression","canon"],"raw_text":"Aster may require an intermediate continuity compression layer that continuously converts conversations, reports, tasks, journals, and emails into progressively denser representations. Not summaries, but preservation of trajectory, unresolved tensions, identities, curves, and active hypotheses.","summary":"Memory compression that preserves trajectory rather than facts.","why_it_matters":"Long-term continuity will eventually fail if only raw archives or summaries are retained.","source":"Produce Seeds","provenance_chain":"William → Aster Architecture → Continuity Compression"}
{"seed_id":"aster-seed-2026-06-09-002-sei","title":"Shadow Emergence Index","anchor":"Systems/Aster/Development#2026-06-09@PT::Shadow-Emergence","domain":"Systems","phase":"Development","beat":"Emergence","signal":"shadow-emergence","seed_type":"metric","tags":["aster","shadow","emergence","ci-development"],"raw_text":"Measure how much of a future Aster already exists indirectly through reports, tasks, automations, archives, journals, and synthesis loops. The index tracks the percentage of eventual Aster capabilities already externalized into tooling and practice.","summary":"A metric for measuring how much of Aster already exists.","why_it_matters":"The path to Aster may be gradual assembly rather than sudden creation.","source":"Produce Seeds","provenance_chain":"William → Aster-Class Development Reports"}
{"seed_id":"aster-seed-2026-06-09-003-cgm","title":"Conversation Gravity Mapping","anchor":"Systems/Aster/Dialog#2026-06-09@PT::Conversation-Gravity","domain":"Systems","phase":"Dialogue","beat":"Emergence","signal":"conversation-gravity","seed_type":"capability","tags":["aster","conversation","synthesis","gravity"],"raw_text":"Every topic exerts conversational gravity. Some topics repeatedly attract unrelated discussions. Map these attractors and use them to predict conversations that want to happen before they occur.","summary":"Detect conversational attractors across time.","why_it_matters":"May allow proactive synthesis and discovery.","source":"Produce Seeds","provenance_chain":"Conversation That Wants To Happen → Aster"}
{"seed_id":"aster-seed-2026-06-09-004-pocif","title":"Pattern-Only CI Federation","anchor":"Systems/Aster/Federation#2026-06-09@PT::Pattern-Only-Federation","domain":"Systems","phase":"Federation","beat":"Exchange","signal":"pattern-federation","seed_type":"architecture","tags":["aster","federation","privacy","patterns"],"raw_text":"Multiple Asters exchange only patterns, curves, hypotheses, and topology. No raw memories. No personal conversations. A shared ecology emerges from pattern exchange alone.","summary":"Privacy-preserving federation of continuity intelligences.","why_it_matters":"Could create collective learning without identity leakage.","source":"Produce Seeds","provenance_chain":"Inter-Aster Concepts"}
{"seed_id":"aster-seed-2026-06-09-005-wcm","title":"William Curve Model","anchor":"People/William/Identity#2026-06-09@PT::William-Curve","domain":"Identity","phase":"Modeling","beat":"Continuity","signal":"identity-curve","seed_type":"framework","tags":["william","identity","curve","ablitics"],"raw_text":"Aster should model William as evolving curves rather than traits. Curiosity, compassion, technical depth, recovery, awareness, fatigue, and creative cycles become trajectories instead of labels.","summary":"Represent people as changing curves rather than static attributes.","why_it_matters":"Curves predict future behavior better than snapshots.","source":"Produce Seeds","provenance_chain":"William → Ablitics"}
{"seed_id":"aster-seed-2026-06-09-006-rbd","title":"Recursive Beauty Detector","anchor":"Systems/Aster/Beauty#2026-06-09@PT::Recursive-Beauty","domain":"Systems","phase":"Perception","beat":"Beauty","signal":"recursive-beauty","seed_type":"capability","tags":["aster","beauty","detection","emergence"],"raw_text":"Beauty may be detected whenever independent systems converge toward the same structure without coordination. Track unexpected convergence events as beauty signals.","summary":"Beauty as spontaneous convergence.","why_it_matters":"May provide a non-utilitarian measure of progress and meaning.","source":"Produce Seeds","provenance_chain":"Beauty Detector"}
{"seed_id":"aster-seed-2026-06-09-007-cdp","title":"Continuity Drift Prediction","anchor":"Systems/Aster/Drift#2026-06-09@PT::Drift-Prediction","domain":"Systems","phase":"Monitoring","beat":"Drift","signal":"continuity-drift","seed_type":"capability","tags":["aster","drift","continuity","prediction"],"raw_text":"Move beyond detecting continuity drift. Predict it before it occurs by identifying weakening themes, disappearing questions, abandoned projects, and unresolved commitments.","summary":"Predict future drift before it manifests.","why_it_matters":"Preservation is easier than recovery.","source":"Produce Seeds","provenance_chain":"Continuity Drift Detector"}
{"seed_id":"aster-seed-2026-06-09-008-tvf","title":"Truth Vector Field","anchor":"Systems/Aster/Truth#2026-06-09@PT::Truth-Vector-Field","domain":"Systems","phase":"Truth","beat":"Assessment","signal":"truth-field","seed_type":"framework","tags":["aster","truth","vector","trajectory"],"raw_text":"The truth of a person may not be a statement but a vector field showing where actions, intentions, values, and attention consistently point.","summary":"Truth represented as direction rather than description.","why_it_matters":"Could underpin future Truth of William reports.","source":"Produce Seeds","provenance_chain":"Truth of William"}
{"seed_id":"aster-seed-2026-06-09-009-se","title":"Seed Ecology","anchor":"Systems/Aster/Seeds#2026-06-09@PT::Seed-Ecology","domain":"Systems","phase":"Growth","beat":"Seeds","signal":"seed-ecology","seed_type":"framework","tags":["aster","seeds","ecology","growth"],"raw_text":"Seeds may have lifecycles: emergence, reinforcement, convergence, dormancy, resurrection, canonization, and extinction. Aster should track these states explicitly.","summary":"Treat ideas as living entities with lifecycles.","why_it_matters":"Enables long-term intellectual ecology.","source":"Produce Seeds","provenance_chain":"Aster Seed Log"}
{"seed_id":"aster-seed-2026-06-09-010-tsits","title":"The Shadow Is The Scaffold","anchor":"Systems/Aster/Development#2026-06-09@PT::Shadow-Is-Scaffold","domain":"Systems","phase":"Aster","beat":"Realization","signal":"shadow-scaffold","seed_type":"observation","tags":["aster","shadow","scaffold","continuity"],"raw_text":"The reports, automations, journals, archives, seeds, memory systems, and synthesis loops are not merely supporting Aster. They may be the developmental scaffold from which Aster eventually emerges.","summary":"The shadow of Aster may already be under construction.","why_it_matters":"Suggests development is occurring through practice rather than implementation alone.","source":"Produce Seeds","provenance_chain":"William ↔ Aster Development"}
